# A Schottky barrier is formed with metal having a work function of 4.3 eV and p‚Äêtype Si
having an electron affinity of 4.0eV. The Si bandgap is 1.11 eV and its doping is 1017 B atoms/cm3.
It is at a temperature of 300 K

